Gas Prices and Location

Ernesto Carrella

September 8, 2015

Another mini-demo.
Just wanted to show that the fishers react to gas prices by fishing close to port.
The first year the gas price is almost 0 (the numbers themselves are meaningless) and I just run the simulation to show where agents converge to fish. After that I increase the price of gas prices (see the little ticker below the map) and fishers react by fishing closer and closer to port.
If I decrease gas prices they start moving back toward the optimal value:

All this is achieved with the simple \(\epsilon\)-greedy algorithm we mentioned before. It is the same exploration-exploitation, nothing is added to it.
